cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.IR

This paper deals with the use of electronic health records (EHR) and machine learning algorithms for selecting clinical tests for esophageal cancer based on patient preferences. This involves classification tasks and algorithm design, which are typical topics in the computer science sub-categories of Computational Engineering (cs.CE), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The use of EHRs also involves data management and retrieval, which are relevant to the sub-categories of Databases (cs.DB) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
